    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "TOLEDO, Ohio \u2013 The Toledo baseball team hit the ball all over the ballpark and received a sturdy effort on the mound from freshman\nHayden Frey\nto take a 17-2 victory in seven innings in the series finale at Scott Park on Sunday.\nThe Rockets (9-9, 5-1 MAC) scored in every inning they batted, exploding for six runs in the fifth and five runs in the sixth. Toledo hit five home runs and drew eight walks. Toledo has won its seventh-straight MAC series, dating back to last season, with a 17-4 conference record in that stretch.\nCharlie Scholvin\ndrove in five runs to lead Toledo offensively, while\nCade Baker\nand\nTroy Sudbrook\neach brought home four. Sudbrook also homered twice, the second multi-home run game of his career. Four Rockets tallied multi-hit games, while five crossed the plate multiple times. Scholvin's five RBIs were a career high.\nFrey (1-0) pitched a complete game In his first career start, allowing just two runs on seven hits. He tallied four strikeouts with just two walks to earn his first career win.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"We took care of business today in a big way. After not playing well yesterday, we challenged our players to finish the weekend with the right focus. They did that. The bats were locked in today, hitting five home runs en route to scoring every inning. Even with all the offense, the highlight of the day was freshman\nHayden Frey\nthrowing a complete game in his first-ever start as a Rocket. He was simply outstanding.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nCade Baker\n\u2013 3-for-4, HR (1), 4 RBIs, 3 runs, 2 2B, 1 BB\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 2-for-4, 2 HR (4), 4 RBIs, 2 runs, 1 BB\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 1-for-3, 5 RBIs, 1 run, 1 BB, 1 SF\nJacob Payne\n\u2013 2-for-3, HR (1), 3 runs, 1 RBI, 1 BB\nCole Cahill\n\u2013 3-for-4, 3 runs, 1 2B, 1 SF\nPitching Lines\nHayden Frey\n(W, 1-0) \u2013 7.0 IP, 7 H, 2 R, 2 ER, 2 BB, 4 Ks\nHow it Happened\nCade Baker\nturned on a pitch to lead off the first with a home run.\nToledo loaded the bases with two outs in the second, before a\nCharlie Scholvin\nwalk and a\nTroy Sudbrook\nhit-by-pitch each scored runs for a 3-0 Toledo lead.\nAfter an NIU run in the third,\nJacob Payne\ncracked a solo home run to left-center for a 4-1 Rockets' edge.\nSudbrook and\nAlex McCranie\nlaunched back-to-back homers in the bottom of the fourth for a 6-1 Toledo advantage.\nThe Rockets batted around in the fifth, scoring six runs on five hits for a 12-2 lead.\nLiam Arsich\nand Baker each produced RBI hits, followed by a two-run single from Scholvin. Sudbrook\u00a0then went to the opposite field for a two-run home run.\nUT tacked on five more runs in the sixth, including\u00a0a two-run double by Baker and a sac fly from\u00a0Scholvin where two runs scored.\nUp Next\nThe Rockets begin the week at Michigan on Tuesday, March 17 at 4:00 p.m. Toledo will then play its first road conference series of the season at Central Michigan on Friday-Sunday, March 20-22."
  },
